==Demographics==
As of the [[census|census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=http://factfinder2.census.gov|publisher=[[United_States_Census_Bureau|United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=American FactFinder}}</ref> of 2000, there were 4,613 people, 1,924 households, and 1,377 families residing in the CDP. The [[population_density|population density]] was 567.9 people per square mile (219.3/km²). There were 2,045 housing units at an average density of 251.8/sq mi (97.2/km²). The racial makeup of the CDP was 97.59% [[White_(U.S._Census)|White]], 0.65% [[African_American_(U.S._Census)|African American]], 0.04% [[Native_American_(U.S._Census)|Native American]], 1.02% [[Asian_(U.S._Census)|Asian]], 0.02% [[Pacific_Islander_(U.S._Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.13% from [[Race_(United_States_Census)|other races]], and 0.54% from two or more races. [[Hispanic_(U.S._Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino_(U.S._Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.48% of the population.

There were 1,924 households out of which 26.7% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 61.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 7.6% had a female householder with no husband present, and 28.4% were non-families. 25.1% of all households were made up of individuals and 14.2% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.38 and the average family size was 2.82.

In the CDP the population was spread out with 20.6% under the age of 18, 7.0% from 18 to 24, 24.3% from 25 to 44, 27.6% from 45 to 64, and 20.6% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 44 years. For every 100 females there were 94.6 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 89.0 males.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $42,911, and the median income for a family was $48,494. Males had a median income of $33,125 versus $23,179 for females. The [[per_capita_income|per capita income]] for the CDP was $20,989. About 4.8% of families and 7.3% of the population were below the [[poverty_line|poverty line]], including 4.9% of those under age 18 and 5.1% of those age 65 or over.

==Library==
The LaVale Public Library is part of the [[Allegany_Country_Library_System|Allegany Country Library System]] and is the headquarters for the Allegany County Bookmobile. The first public library in LaVale opened on April 18, 1953. The current building opened on September 28, 1975.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://home.alleganycountylibrary.info/locations/lavale.htm|title=LaVale Public Library|publisher=Allegany County Library System |accessdate=February 13, 2010}}</ref>

